1941;;Old Mother Riley's Circus;;British;;Thomas Bentley;;Arthur Lucan, Kitty McShane;;comedy;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Old_Mother_Riley%27s_Circus;;Old Mother Riley is the ringmaster after taking over a big top with flagging fortunes. Although the circus is plagued by the disappearance of its owner, and the bailiffs are at the door, the show somehow manages to go on. Money starts to pour in, financial disaster is avoided, and Mother Riley discovers her long-lost daughter is in fact the star of the show.[3]